  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Windows System Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Role and Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Perform antivirus definition and security patches, OS, software and firmware upgrades in the system</li><li>Perform SSL certificate renewal of all certificates used in the system</li><li>Troubleshoot system issues including working with OEM supports to determine cause of issue and rectification plan</li><li>Perform monthly system preventive management health checks and reporting</li><li>Support system deployment changes during off-peak operation hours</li><li>Manage L1 to L3 incident tickets and service requests</li><li>Provide L2 support 24/7 based on scheduled rotation basis</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Candidate</strong></u></p><ul><li>Windows Server 2019 and above</li><li>Windows AD, user administration, management of GPO policies</li><li>Windows CA and SSL certificates renewal</li><li>Windows WSUS offline, WSUS manual catalogue import for windows security patch management</li><li>Symantec EndPoint Protection (SEP), SEPM and Symantec LiveUpdate Administrator (LUA)</li><li>VMware ESXi 7U3 and above, VMware VSAN stretch cluster, vCenter, NSX</li><li>Splunk Enterprise, Kiwi Syslog Server, syslog protocol for centralized log collection</li><li>Concepts of SSL certificates such as certificate, keys and cryptographic ciphers</li><li>Degree holder with 5+ years of experience</li></ul>",
